{"word":"διάτορος","slug":"διάτορος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διάτορος</b></el> <el>(διά-τορος, ον) </el>adj (dia-tor os_on) <p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τείρω'><el>τείρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>piercing, galling</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>δ. φόβος</el> <i>thrilling</i> fear, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; of a trumpet, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>pierced, bored through</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}